Installation:

    git clone https://github.com/Leeheng86/shell_cfg.git ~/.rc
    pip install --user git+git://github.com/powerline/powerline

Create symlinks:

    ln -s ~/.rc/bashrc ~/.bashrc
    ln -s ~/.rc/zshrc ~/.zshrc
    ln -s ~/.rc/profile ~/.profile
    ln -s ~/.rc/tmux.conf ~/.tmux.conf
    ln -s ~/.rc/claude/settings.json ~/.claude/settings.json
    ln -s ~/.rc/claude/mcp.json ~/.claude/mcp.json
    ln -s ~/.rc/claude/statusline-command.sh ~/.claude/statusline-command.sh

Claude config:

    All Claude Code settings are in claude/. settings.json is symlinked
    to ~/.claude/settings.json.

    MCP server configs are in claude/mcp.json. API keys are referenced
    as environment variables (e.g. $MY_API_KEY). Store the actual values
    in claude/.secrets (gitignored) as export statements, they will be
    sourced automatically by common.sh.

Shell config:

    All settings are in common.sh. Both bashrc and zshrc source it,
    so changes only need to be made in one place.

Adding or deleting tmux powerline segments by modifying:

On Mac
    vim ~/Library/Python/3.x/lib/python/site-packages/powerline/config_files/themes/tmux/default.json

On Ubuntu
    vim ~/.local/lib/python3.x/site-packages/powerline/config_files/themes/tmux/default.json
